				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How much downtime is needed for a facelift?</h3>
					<p>Most patients need two to three weeks of recovery time after a facelift. During this period, you may experience swelling and bruising, which gradually subsides. Most patients feel comfortable returning to social activities after two weeks. Dr. Johar provides detailed recovery instructions to ensure optimal healing.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the cost difference between surgical and non-surgical options?</h3>
					<p>Non-surgical treatments have lower upfront costs but require regular maintenance. Surgical procedures are more expensive initially but offer longer-lasting results, making them potentially more cost-effective over time. Dr. Johar provides transparent pricing during consultations to help you make an informed decision.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>At what age should I consider facial rejuvenation?</h3>
					<p>There is no specific age for facial rejuvenation. Non-surgical treatments can be beneficial as early as your late 20s for preventive care, while surgical procedures are typically considered from your 40s onward. The best time depends on your individual concerns and goals, which can be discussed during a consultation with Dr. Johar.</p>
